# RepoCoder Studio

A **repository-aware AI coding assistant** built as a phased capstone project. It automates
documentation, generates code from natural language, translates between languages, understands
repository structure, grounds outputs with retrieval-augmented generation (RAG), and orchestrates
multi-step workflows with agents.

> **Preferred model:** [Qwen2.5-Coder](https://huggingface.co/Qwen). See
> [`docs/02_model_comparison.md`](docs/02_model_comparison.md) for why, and where other models
> (CodeGen, DeepSeek-Coder, CodeParrot) fit.

---

## Phased, branch-per-stage design

This repo is built **incrementally**: each stage lives on its own git branch, branched off the
previous one, so `stage-N` contains all the code from stages `1..N`.

| Branch | Stage | What it adds |
|---|---|---|
| `main` | — | Docs, shared utilities (`src/repocoder/common`), skeleton + configs for all stages |
| `stage-1-documentation` | 1 | Code → docstrings/summaries (CodeGen-350M) |
| `stage-2-nl2python` | 2 | Natural language → Python (Qwen2.5-Coder vs DeepSeek-Coder) |
| `stage-3-py2java` | 3 | Python → Java translation |
| `stage-4-repo-awareness` | 4 | AST indexing + repository retrieval (Tree-Sitter) |
| `stage-5-rag` | 5 | Retrieval-augmented generation (FAISS + reranker) |
| `stage-6-agentic` | 6 | Multi-agent orchestration (LangGraph) |

```bash
git checkout stage-1-documentation   # work on a specific stage
git log --oneline --graph --all       # see the incremental history
```

---

## Three phases

1. **Phase 1 — Foundations (Stages 1–3):** baseline documentation, code synthesis, and translation.
2. **Phase 2 — Integration & Accuracy (Stages 4–5):** repository awareness and RAG grounding.
3. **Phase 3 — Generalizability (Stage 6):** agentic orchestration of the building blocks above.

---

## Quick start

### On Google Colab (recommended for Stages 1–3)
Open `notebooks/stageN_*.ipynb` in Colab. The first cell installs that stage's requirements;
the rest call into `src/repocoder`. See [`docs/01_compute_platforms.md`](docs/01_compute_platforms.md)
for platform trade-offs and per-stage recommendations.

### Local / Kaggle / Lightning AI
```bash
python -m venv .venv && source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements/base.txt
pip install -r requirements/stage1.txt          # the stage you're running
pip install -e .                                  # makes `repocoder` importable
python -m scripts.run_stage --stage 1 --config configs/stage1.yaml --limit 5
```

The code auto-detects whether it runs on Colab, Kaggle, or locally (`src/repocoder/common/env.py`)
and resolves cache/data paths accordingly — the same code runs everywhere.

---

## Repository layout

```
docs/         Engineering documentation (platforms, model comparison, envs, challenges, per-stage)
requirements/ base.txt + additive stageN.txt
configs/      stageN.yaml — model id, dataset, generation params, metric toggles
src/repocoder/
  common/     Shared, reusable: env detection, model loading, generation, metrics, io
  stageN_*/   data.py (load) · run.py (generate) · evaluate.py (score)
scripts/      run_stage.py — single CLI entrypoint for any stage
notebooks/    Thin Colab wrappers per stage
tests/        CPU-only smoke tests (tiny models / synthetic fixtures, no GPU needed)
```

